#eNCA speaks to Eddy Mokobodi from Sakisa Energy and Technology group. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Independent power producer, Sakisa Energy and Technology, is urging South Africans to be aware of safety hazards when going off the grid. This as the demand and need for alternative power supply in the country continues to grow. READ:Â Budget 2023 | Govt to incentivise renewable energy Sakisa's director Eddy Mokobodi says those looking for alternative power should only use tried and trusted service providers. Mokobodi said, "if the job is not done correctly then you're at risk for anything that might happen." "Solar panels, batteries and inverters are things that works with electricity. The best way to safeguard yourself is to check the track record or the company." "Check that you're dealing with a competent person."